5: Like I SAID, I didn't do anything!
12:
You know this guy? He just waltzed
in here and stole my guest's wallet!
15: Huh?! There must be some mistake...
18:
You rats are working together, aren't
you!
25:
Can we bring things down a notch?
Go ahead and call in the Guild
Knights, if you want.
35:
Wait! Should we not hear what
Nimbus has to say?
51:
*sniff* Isn't anybody listening? I can
help with this case!
62:
The name's Lucille, traveling future
sleuth and assistant to a
magnificent detective!
71: I'm the one on trial here, kid...
79:
Are you people crazy?! You think a
child will resolve this?
83:
Let's contact the Guild Knights too,
just in case...
89:
Now then. If you would be so kind as
to recount what happened, Mr.
Nimbus?
93:
Well... I got back before anyone else
and thought I'd wait around on the
sofa over there.
95:
The next thing I knew these guys
were waking me up and calling me
a thief. Nobody else around to
blame, I guess.
100: I see, I see! In that case, hmm...
103:
My good sir! Was this sofa of yours
purchased recently?
106:
Yeah... Three days ago, in fact. Had it
custom-made.
109:
Mr. Nimbus, would you please give
this part of the sofa a good kick?
113:
No need to worry! I'll take full
responsibility for any damages.
116:
Lucille... we can't just kick this man's
sofa...
128:
Huh?! That's the guy I bought the
sofa from!
131:
Gotcha red-handed, mister! You
must have waited for Mr. Nimbus to
doze off to make your move, huh!
140:
I'm honestly pretty impressed. I
never would have thought a crook
was hiding in the sofa itself.
144:
Elementary, my dear Alk! The same
thing happened in one of my
favorite mystery novels!
149: You sure you weren't reading horror?
152:
Anyway, thanks for saving Nimbus!
Could we treat you to dinner as a
thank-you?
156: B-but... I didn't do anything special...
161:
Not your average snot-nosed brat,
huh? Relax, kid, it's on us!
169:
By the way, Lucille. You said you
were traveling?
173:
That's right! I've gotta train my skills
if I want to be a great detective
someday!
176:
Master used to teach me, but he
disappeared one day...
180:
But I'll be all right! As long as I
become a great detective too,
Master will definitely return!
183:
So... I have to solve as many cases
as I can, and then some!
187: Well, Stella? What do you say?
191:
Of course. We'd be happy to have
you, Lucille.
205:
...Uh, no, I mean, uh... I'm fine on my
own, you know? I'm the assistant of
a great detective after all.
213:
Flying solo is tough, don't you think?
Besides, we could use a detective
like you.
218: Y-you're really pushy, you know that?
220:
I guess I have no choice! I'll help you
out!
224: ...I know I'll make you proud, Master!
